snippet.textDisplay: It is a mix of Sambalpuri (one dialect of Odiya), Odiya (rituraj portion) and tamil (rap). The original song is the highest recorded song of its time. Many W.B. people find it familiar as this song later recorded by a Kolkata company for marketing. The male version is the anthem of Odisha. But everybody can relate its to thier respective motherland. That is why the goosebumps.
